303
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:23,917
- It was a good start for beginners.
- Everybody out, everybody home.

304
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:41,353
Mini?
How much 12.7 ammo did you fire?

305
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:45,991
- A lot.
- You're damn right.

306
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:54,880
This is a bit heavy.

307
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:59,558
When I got into the barn,
the chickens attacked me.

308
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:03,748
When is the bread done?

309
00:37:35,840 --> 00:37:38,752
Why do we have to do this shit?

310
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:07,635
Ranger.

311
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,038
Look at this, Mads.

312
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:34,153
Even if you have a gun,
I'd still win.

313
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:38,154
- It depends on how far away you are.
- Here.

314
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:42,711
Let's see who draws first.

315
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:46,270
You have to release yours,
I just have to swing this.

316
00:38:46,440 --> 00:38:49,557
From down there?

317
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:54,236
- Can I carry it ...?
- No. Then I'd be like this.

318
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:59,633
Kim, you can lift it with one hand,
right? Or do you need two hands?

319
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:05,192
- Ready?
- Gotcha.

320
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:09,837
Three shots to the chest.

321
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:24,228
- Quite cool ...
- It doesn't get much better than that.

322
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:31,148
- See you later, Mads.
- Send my regards.

323
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:52,958
Alright, Mads?

324
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:59,518
- I'll close off those streets.
- Fine.

325
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:01,830
Mini, over there with Kim.

326
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:08,870
- Why are you with them?
- He's American.

327
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:13,079
- Why are you with them?
- He's red, too.

328
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:16,789
Get out of the military. Leave.

329
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:20,748
- Leave?
- Yes. Go home.

330
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:23,195
Do you have a home?

331
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:26,955
I don't owe you any money,
if that's what you're saying.

332
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:32,232
He has funny eyes.
He is slant-eyed.

333
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:35,153
They look puffy.

334
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:38,589
He took it in the ass.

335
00:41:13,160 --> 00:41:18,598
I regret your losses,
but you all know -

336
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:23,880
- that we have to walk in the fields.

337
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:31,958
How should we know?
Is it our fault, maybe?

338
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:35,719
Last year they bombarded our house.

339
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:39,111
I swear by God I don't even
have any clothes to wear.

340
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:42,033
And my sons cannot help me.

341
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:51,549
Then we must leave our villages.
What can we do?

342
00:41:53,080 --> 00:41:57,551
What can we do? It's not you
or the Taliban that gets killed.

343
00:41:57,720 --> 00:42:00,393
We are the ones who get killed.

344
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:05,549
The civilians get killed.
We sit in our homes and get bombed.

345
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:10,748
The Taliban shoot, and then
they run away. They escape.

346
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:16,995
We're sorry, but we try
to move the war up north.

347
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:21,073
That would be good for us,
for this ruins everything.

348
00:42:27,880 --> 00:42:31,475
You can't.

349
00:42:32,720 --> 00:42:37,635
People fight, because they're poor.
Including the Taliban.

350
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:51,548
- Come on, you faggots.
- Look who's talking.

351
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:55,269
You planted bombs, you ape!

352
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:33,675
So far we know that a civilian car
approached the gas station -

353
00:43:33,840 --> 00:43:39,312
- on Highway 1 towards the desert,
the route we usually take home.

354
00:43:39,480 --> 00:43:42,790
The car hit something
and detonated.

355
00:43:42,960 --> 00:43:49,149
There was an explosion.
Our formation is vehicle 1 in front..

356
00:43:49,320 --> 00:43:52,869
Primarily observe
from the rifleman's position.

357
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:57,079
We'll see how bad it is
when we get there. Okay?

358
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:05,158
Flip your night vision down
and keep a lookout behind.

359
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:23,918
On our way back from there
I heard a huge explosion.

360
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:26,355
I couldn't believe it.

361
00:44:26,520 --> 00:44:29,751
I ran back down -

362
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:35,119
- and 7-5 and 3-5 ran right into me,
so I went flying.

363
00:44:35,280 --> 00:44:38,272
Everybody was running
all over the place.

364
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:42,149
Then I heard, "There's
blood everywhere. 2-5 is down."

365
00:44:51,480 --> 00:44:55,359
I said, "For fuck's sake, 5.
You should keep your head down."

366
00:44:55,520 --> 00:45:00,753
Then he said, "I know.
How about a dance?" I cracked up.

367
00:45:00,920 --> 00:45:06,552
"This isn't a good time."
Then I gave him emotional first aid.

368
00:45:06,720 --> 00:45:10,395
He had a huge gash here.
Turned out to be a fractured skull.

369
00:45:10,560 --> 00:45:13,632
Damn.

370
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:17,831
- No fucking fun.
- I'll say.

371
00:45:24,960 --> 00:45:29,511
I heard a massive boom,
and everything was sand and dust -

372
00:45:29,680 --> 00:45:32,240
- for a few seconds.

373
00:45:32,400 --> 00:45:37,872
I tried to feel if my teeth were broken
with my tongue -

374
00:45:38,040 --> 00:45:43,353
- and I tried to wiggle my fingers.
I couldn't tell if my teeth were okay -

375
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:47,513
- because I had so much gravel,
sand and blood in my mouth.

376
00:45:47,680 --> 00:45:53,152
I only felt splinters and stones.
I didn't know what was what.

377
00:45:53,320 --> 00:45:57,438
I tried ... I don't remember clearly -

378
00:45:57,600 --> 00:46:02,879
- but I looked down
and saw two trickles of blood.

379
00:46:03,040 --> 00:46:06,874
It wasn't until I was
in the helicopter -

380
00:46:07,040 --> 00:46:10,715
- that I started to get
really uncomfortable.

381
00:46:10,880 --> 00:46:14,634
That's when I had time
to think about it.

382
00:46:14,800 --> 00:46:17,917
"What do I look like now?
Will I ever recover?"

383
00:46:18,080 --> 00:46:23,518
"Will I talk funny for the rest
of my life?" All those questions.

384
00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:30,916
I have to go back to Armadillo
and stand in front of them all -

385
00:46:31,080 --> 00:46:34,959
- and say, "You can't
get rid of me that easily."

386
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:49,796
- <i>2-5 here.</i>
- Raven has something.

387
00:46:49,960 --> 00:46:54,033
Three men are walking south.
62.7, 31.4.

388
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:58,910
