00:55:53,440 --> 00:55:57,911
She had abdominal injuries.

467
00:55:58,080 --> 00:56:02,358
And a fractured skull.

468
00:56:10,240 --> 00:56:14,028
That's your target.

469
00:56:14,200 --> 00:56:17,795
I did what we had planned.

470
00:56:23,400 --> 00:56:26,358
There's nothing to do about it.

471
00:56:26,520 --> 00:56:29,796
It's ... I almost said 'spilt milk'.

472
00:56:29,960 --> 00:56:33,635
Harsh words, but that's what it is.

473
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:39,033
It can't be undone,
and you shouldn't blame yourself.

474
00:56:41,280 --> 00:56:44,829
We live in a world,
where you watch the news -

475
00:56:45,000 --> 00:56:48,675
- with thousands of people,
who die all the time ...

476
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:52,833
So it doesn't bother me if a girl dies.
It's just because you're close to it.

477
00:56:53,000 --> 00:56:57,232
I just think ... We came down here,
and it wasn't done on purpose.

478
00:56:57,400 --> 00:57:01,678
We did exactly what we're supposed
to do, and we would do it again.

479
00:57:01,840 --> 00:57:03,159
That's the way it is.

480
00:57:08,360 --> 00:57:15,596
I'm very tired. My house was burnt
down, and that's why I'm here.

481
00:57:18,640 --> 00:57:23,873
My mother died,
and so did my little child.

482
00:57:29,600 --> 00:57:36,039
We were away. Only my mother
and the little one stayed at home.

483
00:57:36,200 --> 00:57:40,671
I told my mother to come along,
but she didn't want to.

484
00:57:51,400 --> 00:57:56,269
You have to tell us
which things were destroyed.

485
00:57:56,440 --> 00:58:02,709
Quilts, matresses, curtains, plates and
lots of other things in my house.

486
00:58:09,840 --> 00:58:13,913
May God forgive your mother.
She has become a martyr.

487
00:58:31,120 --> 00:58:36,353
Mini, observe for the fucking platoon.
A situation is reported -

488
00:58:36,520 --> 00:58:39,193
- but they move forward anyway.

489
00:58:47,560 --> 00:58:50,393
Let's get the fuck out of here!

490
00:58:52,120 --> 00:58:53,838
Wait!

491
00:58:54,000 --> 00:58:55,399
Oh no ...!

492
00:58:57,680 --> 00:59:00,638
Say something, man!

493
00:59:02,120 --> 00:59:06,477
Is everyone okay? Over.

494
00:59:06,640 --> 00:59:11,395
Negative, negative.
Condition critical.

495
00:59:11,560 --> 00:59:16,793
He can talk, but has
difficulty breathing. Over.

496
00:59:18,280 --> 00:59:23,479
Copy that. Get him to my position
quickly. I'll get ready here.

497
00:59:25,360 --> 00:59:28,193
Fuck ...! Here we go.

498
00:59:28,400 --> 00:59:33,155
3-4 here. The helicopter
will be here in two minutes.

499
00:59:33,320 --> 00:59:39,316
Copy. We'll start moving him
to pick-up point. Over.

500
00:59:39,480 --> 00:59:43,837
We've sent our call signs
minus four men -

501
00:59:44,000 --> 00:59:47,675
- who're picking up the last bits.

502
00:59:47,840 --> 00:59:53,756
We have a vehicle to secure us
and expect to arrive in ten. Over.

503
01:00:17,080 --> 01:00:23,269
His condition is stable, but his
left leg was amputated at the thigh -

504
01:00:23,440 --> 01:00:27,831
- and his right leg below the knee.

505
01:00:29,400 --> 01:00:32,631
He was wounded in the groin -

506
01:00:32,800 --> 01:00:38,318
- and in the abdomen,
but there was no internal bleeding.

507
01:00:38,480 --> 01:00:44,157
They think he'll survive,
but he was seriously wounded.

508
01:00:46,040 --> 01:00:50,636
They've found our weak points
and are making the most of them.

509
01:00:50,800 --> 01:00:55,032
Yes, we're good at attacking
and moving forward -

510
01:00:55,200 --> 01:01:00,069
- but we're held back because
of those damn IEDs we can't find.

511
01:01:06,120 --> 01:01:09,715
It's all fucked up.

512
01:01:09,880 --> 01:01:14,749
When you think about it,
you wouldn't feel guilty about -

513
01:01:14,920 --> 01:01:21,029
- shooting those assholes.
I'd feel worse shooting a stray dog.

514
01:01:22,080 --> 01:01:24,640
Right.

515
01:02:29,920 --> 01:02:33,754
On our way back from patrol
we were told -

516
01:02:33,920 --> 01:02:38,516
- that three men from Romeo 1-5
hit an IED on Highway 1.

517
01:02:38,680 --> 01:02:44,789
At that point, they were category B,
which is seriously wounded.

518
01:02:44,960 --> 01:02:49,795
When we got back here,
we were told all three were dead.

519
01:02:50,960 --> 01:02:54,316
I think everyone was hoping -

520
01:02:54,480 --> 01:03:00,794
- that we would go down in history
as the first team not to lose a man.

521
01:03:06,560 --> 01:03:11,714
Then they showed pictures of those
three handsome young men -

522
01:03:11,880 --> 01:03:17,716
- who were smiling,
and whose eyes were shining.

523
01:03:17,880 --> 01:03:24,228
They looked happy. I can't take
much more of this, Mads.

524
01:03:24,400 --> 01:03:27,597
- It's really, really hard.
- Yes.

525
01:03:30,000 --> 01:03:33,470
Please be careful.

526
01:03:36,280 --> 01:03:39,590
Come home soon.

527
01:03:39,760 --> 01:03:44,231
I will.
Another two months to go.

528
01:03:46,800 --> 01:03:50,395
Let's commemorate
our three fellow men -

529
01:03:50,560 --> 01:03:55,680
- and honor them and show
our respect with a minute of silence.

530
01:04:35,280 --> 01:04:39,353
The men are getting tired.
Wahir, where we were doing well -

531
01:04:39,520 --> 01:04:44,799
- is now infiltrated by the Taliban.

532
01:04:46,120 --> 01:04:50,193
They know exactly
how many we are in the camp -

533
01:04:50,360 --> 01:04:55,912
- and when we're up to something
or not. We'll have to see ...

534
01:04:57,680 --> 01:05:02,037
...if ambushing them will work.

535
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:11,276
Is anyone too upset to go?

536
01:05:11,440 --> 01:05:14,113
- I'd like to stay home.
- Me, too.

537
01:05:14,280 --> 01:05:18,796
Mads, are you okay?
You don't mind going?

538
01:05:23,600 --> 01:05:28,310
Well, if you need me,
I'll come along.

539
01:05:28,480 --> 01:05:30,038
Great.

540
01:06:09,560 --> 01:06:15,351
Go get the job done.
You know what to do, so be careful.

541
01:06:15,520 --> 01:06:18,830
Give them hell in the morning.
That's the whole point.

542
01:06:19,000 --> 01:06:23,232
See you tomorrow.
Safe journey.

543
01:07:34,680 --> 01:07:39,515
One group of enemy forces
reported ready. Over.

544
01:07:42,960 --> 01:07:47,670
Several civilians
are heading your way.

545
01:07:47,840 --> 01:07:51,753
On the right-hand side
of the men in the back.

546
01:07:53,440 --> 01:07:57,035
Women and children
are leaving the zone.

547
01:07:57,200 --> 01:08:02,149
There are several combat indicators.
More families are leaving the zone.

548
01:08:03,360 --> 01:08:05,396
There's no mistaking that.

549
01:08:06,320 --> 01:08:12,236
Okay, the last ICOM says they've
spotted our patrol and will ambush it.

550
01:08:16,280 --> 01:08:20,478
I have a possible digger
about 200-250m north of me -

551
01:08:20,640 --> 01:08:24,428
- at a compound.
Request warning shot. Over.

552
01:08:24,600 --> 01:08:27,433
Copy. Stand by.

553
01:08:32,120 --> 01:08:36,557
- It's a damn kill zone out there.
- Fine with me, as long as they shoot.

554
01:09:03,920 --> 01:09:07,833
All those on the right,
return to the trees.

555
01:09:12,160 --> 01:09:16,631
3, retreat to the compound wall.

556
01:09:26,480 --> 01:09:33,079
- What did you do so far?
- I gave him morphine in the thigh.

557
01:09:33,240 --> 01:09:38,553
And I gave him Fentanyl.
His pulse was fine.

558
01:09:46,160 --> 01:09:49,470
- Can he have a drink?
- Yes.

559
01:10:14,240 --> 01:10:17,038
Where the hell are those bastards?

560
01:10:18,440 --> 01:10:21,432
- Give me a fucking Taliban, man.
- Forward!

561
01:10:24,960 --> 01:10:27,758
Let's go, move forward.

562
01:10:35,480 --> 01:10:40,031
- Fuck, they almost got me!
- Cover for fuck's sake! Cover!

563
01:10:44,440 --> 01:10:46,590
I can't hear you.

564
01:10:46,760 --> 01:10:50,196
We're in the open field.
Where are you?

565
01:10:50,360 --> 01:10:53,989
You're on my right
in the open field.

566
01:10:54,160 --> 01:10:59,393
- Hold your fire!
- 3, you're shooting at the trees.

567
01:10:59,560 --> 01:11:04,588
- I'm on the other side, you idiot.
- The Taliban are in the ditch.

568
01:11:04,760 --> 01:11:07,672
What the fuck is he talking about?

569
01:11:07,840 --> 01:11:11,150
The Taliban are
in the ditch in front of you.

570
01:11:11,320 --> 01:11:14,198
- Right in front of us!
- Daniel!

571
01:11:14,360 --> 01:11:16,920
- Can you get him with a grenade?
- Yes.

572
01:11:17,080 --> 01:11:19,469
Fire in the hole!

573
01:11:24,800 --> 01:11:28,395
Now we neutralize them.
Kim, over here!

574
01:11:32,840 --> 01:11:37,755
- You're walking towards each other.
- Frederik was hit!

575
01:11:37,920 --> 01:11:41,276
- There's another one here.
- Frederik was hit in the leg.

576
01:11:41,440 --> 01:11:44,671
- Who?
- Frederik. He's lying out here.

577
01:11:46,640 --> 01:11:51,236
- Who was hit?
- Frederik. He's lying out here.

578
01:11:52,800 --> 01:11:57,032
- Kim ...! Go help Frederik.
- Hold your fire!

579
01:11:59,800 --> 01:12:03,315
- Here we are, Frederik.
- Is that guy dead, or what?

580
01:12:03,480 --> 01:12:07,996
Frederik, if you can limp,
then let's get over to that building.

581
01:12:08,160 --> 01:12:10,879
- Super.
- Where to ...?

582
01:12:11,040 --> 01:12:14,032
- Where to?
- To your right.

583
01:12:16,240 --> 01:12:19,198
Stay here.
I'll take him.

584
01:12:30,440 --> 01:12:34,877
Hey! There's one more here!
And two more over there!

585
01:12:37,200 --> 01:12:40,988
- Easy, easy ...
- They have to fucking die!

586
01:12:41,160 --> 01:12:44,197
- He's already on his way.
- Good job!

587
01:12:48,400 --> 01:12:51,790
- There are three dead over there.
- Move on, Daniel!

588
01:12:51,960 --> 01:12:54,838
They fired from the corner over there.

589
01:12:58,360 --> 01:13:01,432
As soon as we've cleaned up, we ...

590
01:13:06,680 --> 01:13:09,558
5, I've got a hand-grenade.

591
01:13:16,040 --> 01:13:20,556
- I need you to check my arm.
- What the hell ...? Your arm?

592
01:13:20,720 --> 01:13:23,234
Look at this ...

593
01:13:23,400 --> 01:13:27,439
- It was stuck in my soft armor.
- Your soft armor?

594
01:13:27,600 --> 01:13:31,070
- Where precisely?
- Look, it's ...

595
01:13:31,280 --> 01:13:35,478
- And through here. And there.
- Shit.

596
01:13:37,600 --> 01:13:41,354
- Damn, that was crazy!
- Hole is cleaned!

597
01:13:41,520 --> 01:13:44,114
Fucking pigs, man!

598
01:13:46,240 --> 01:13:48,708
- Alright?
- Yes.

599
01:13:50,560 --> 01:13:53,313
Good.
Keep your hand still.

600
01:14:01,120 --> 01:14:04,112
Try holding it upwards.

601
01:14:06,520 --> 01:14:09,398
- 30 seconds ...
- 30 seconds.

602
01:14:48,520 --> 01:14:51,990
- Damn, that was crazy.
- There are five dead in the ditch.

603
01:14:52,160 --> 01:14:54,958
Five dead Taliban right there?

604
01:14:55,120 --> 01:14:58,351
This feels completely surreal.

605
01:14:59,400 --> 01:15:03,678
- Where are those assholes?
- I shot this one in the head.

606
01:15:05,520 --> 01:15:08,956
- Damn, it stinks.
- Shut up.

607
01:15:12,680 --> 01:15:15,240
- Let go of it.
- There's one more.

608
01:15:15,400 --> 01:15:19,109
- Wait a sec. You cover me!
- Of course.

609
01:15:19,280 --> 01:15:25,150
This will be messy. Oh, you went
commando, you sick bastard.

610
01:15:28,520 --> 01:15:33,389
- Are those hand guns or magazines?
- He had a pistol apparently.

611
01:15:44,280 --> 01:15:46,874
They already stink.

612
01:15:49,120 --> 01:15:53,159
Kim, if you've tried slaughtering
animals, this is no big deal.

613
01:15:53,320 --> 01:15:56,232
That's a bit much, isn't it?

614
01:15:56,400 --> 01:15:58,630
No guns.

615
01:15:59,840 --> 01:16:03,833
It's a good thing
they aren't any heavier.

616
01:16:05,240 --> 01:16:07,435
What are you packing, buddy?

617
01:16:11,000 --> 01:16:14,959
Okay, get ready to move forward.

618
01:16:27,760 --> 01:16:31,116
How many shots did you fire?
You really went at it.

619
01:16:31,280 --> 01:16:36,798
- Don't they deserve to die?
- Sure. I don't feel sorry for them.

620
01:16:43,920 --> 01:16:48,914
- The water in the stream was red.
- "There's no one there."

621
01:16:49,080 --> 01:16:52,231
"Yes, there is!"
Then you figured it out.

622
01:16:52,400 --> 01:16:57,155
It was a ricochet. It nicked me
and was stopped there.

623
01:16:57,320 --> 01:17:00,198
I have the bullet in my pocket.

624
01:17:00,360 --> 01:17:04,717
- 40 seconds.
- Pancake!

625
01:17:13,320 --> 01:17:15,038
Way to go!

626
01:17:26,280 --> 01:17:29,158
- Welcome. We have sodas.
- Sounds good.

627
01:17:29,320 --> 01:17:33,677
Great job.
That was fucking awesome.

628
01:17:33,840 --> 01:17:37,719
- Four of them with a fucking grenade.
- It was nice.

629
01:17:37,880 --> 01:17:42,078
Fuck, that was great.
This is something we'll never forget.

630
01:17:42,240 --> 01:17:46,791
That was some of the best
fucking soldiering I've ever seen.

631
01:17:46,960 --> 01:17:49,679
You did a damn good job.

632
01:17:49,840 --> 01:17:53,355
They didn't have any ID
or cell phones on them.

633
01:17:53,520 --> 01:17:58,389
I had to pull one of them
by the head from under a log.

634
01:17:58,560 --> 01:18:02,678
- He was stuck underneath it.
- Yuck. All the dead Afghans.

635
01:18:02,840 --> 01:18:07,197
Mini, your eyes were huge.
You just stood there staring at them.

636
01:18:07,360 --> 01:18:10,909
The worst thing was with 3.
"They are in the creek."

637
01:18:11,080 --> 01:18:15,358
I didn't believe them, but emptied
a magazine down the creek.

638
01:18:15,520 --> 01:18:19,832
"They're still there!"
"No, there's nobody there."

639
01:18:20,000 --> 01:18:24,391
Hand grenade! I came up, there were
four of them lying there, rattling.

640
01:18:25,840 --> 01:18:31,039
Then 5 wanted to be in on it, so
he emptied a magazine under the log.

641
01:18:31,200 --> 01:18:36,274
- Then Signaler and I found one more.
- Yeah, he said so.

642
01:18:36,440 --> 01:18:40,831
- Not much fun for those Talibobs.
- They were in a bad spot.

643
01:18:41,720 --> 01:18:46,510
Olby, you say four on the first side?
Plus two more on the other side.

644
01:18:46,680 --> 01:18:49,240
- No, only one.
- There were two.

645
01:18:49,400 --> 01:18:54,474
Wasn't there one farther along?
When we turned the corner -

646
01:18:54,640 --> 01:18:59,873
- I'm sure we fired at two of them.
- I searched the whole lot.

647
01:19:00,040 --> 01:19:06,832
You went back? Okay. Well, no one
crawled away after we were there.

648
01:19:20,240 --> 01:19:26,236
Good afternoon.
Everyone's back from the Green Zone.

649
01:19:26,400 --> 01:19:31,076
It was a hectic morning.
I think we all agree on that.

650
01:19:31,240 --> 01:19:36,075
The wounded are doing alright.
I have a fresh update on them.

651
01:19:36,240 --> 01:19:40,916
- Both were operated on.
- Louder!

652
01:19:41,080 --> 01:19:46,029
One of them in the shoulder,
the other in the leg.

653
01:19:46,200 --> 01:19:51,797
Grejs says he's sorry
he won't be coming back.

654
01:19:51,960 --> 01:19:58,354
He's going back to Denmark for
rehabilitation. That's all we know.

655
01:19:59,400 --> 01:20:05,475
You did a good job
and showed guts, 2nd platoon.

656
01:20:05,640 --> 01:20:08,279
Today was a close shave.

657
01:20:09,680 --> 01:20:12,513
Anything else?
Have a nice day.

658
01:20:19,640 --> 01:20:23,235
- War booty!
- Loots of war!

659
01:20:26,400 --> 01:20:30,712
Let's start the debriefing.

660
01:20:30,880 --> 01:20:35,749
I want to get through it quickly,
and get to the point.

661
01:20:35,920 --> 01:20:41,597
Today we can establish
that we didn't fire at each other.

662
01:20:41,760 --> 01:20:45,435
There were many instances,
where we were in doubt -

663
01:20:45,600 --> 01:20:47,795
- and mistakes have happened.

664
01:20:47,960 --> 01:20:52,397
I had my doubts that
the enemy was only 3m away.

665
01:20:52,560 --> 01:20:57,031
I hear you hollering
that he's close by, and I say "No!"

666
01:20:57,200 --> 01:21:03,196
In the end I was so irritated that I
emptied a magazine down the stream.

667
01:21:03,360 --> 01:21:07,069
I thought that would be enough,
but you said no -

668
01:21:07,240 --> 01:21:10,869
- and that's when
we threw a grenade.

669
01:21:11,040 --> 01:21:14,157
Afterwards Signaler and I -

670
01:21:14,320 --> 01:21:20,634
- found four men groaning heavily
in the ditch, feeling rather bad.

671
01:21:20,800 --> 01:21:26,716
We liquidated them
in the most humane way possible.

672
01:21:26,880 --> 01:21:31,237
5 joined in and fired a magazine
under a little bridge -

673
01:21:31,400 --> 01:21:34,915
- and we cleaned the area
and found the shooter Ian mentioned.

674
01:21:35,080 --> 01:21:41,474
- He was hit and moaning.
- He was trying to crawl.

675
01:21:41,640 --> 01:21:46,191
- We shot him 30-40 times.
- We finished them off.

676
01:21:46,360 --> 01:21:47,759
- Thanks!
- That was it.

677
01:22:44,680 --> 01:22:48,514
It was fucking awesome.
Not while it was happening -

678
01:22:48,680 --> 01:22:53,435
- but when we got back. Now we've
been at war. Now we've tried it.

679
01:22:53,600 --> 01:22:58,594
I never felt that way on patrol
before. Normally it's just boring.

680
01:22:58,760 --> 01:23:01,035
But this time I thought -

681
01:23:01,200 --> 01:23:06,399
- there was a real risk
of being boxed in.

682
01:23:06,560 --> 01:23:10,553
I never thought that before.
We outnumber them -

683
01:23:10,720 --> 01:23:14,633
- and have cool weapons, so they
can't touch us. But here they could.

684
01:23:16,440 --> 01:23:21,673
But I'd still like to try it again.
One more time.

685
01:23:21,840 --> 01:23:24,434
I wouldn't.

686
01:23:24,600 --> 01:23:30,038
Think about it! When your tour is over,
you'll feel so much better about it.

687
01:23:31,800 --> 01:23:34,394
- Yes.
- It's true.

688
01:23:34,560 --> 01:23:38,678
Making a difference
is a cool feeling.

689
01:23:38,840 --> 01:23:43,197
Having been up shit creek
will feel great once you're back home.

690
01:23:43,360 --> 01:23:48,798
Imagine if our tour was just a load
of crap with nothing going on -

691
01:23:48,960 --> 01:23:51,872
- and only boring patrols.

692
01:23:52,040 --> 01:23:56,272
- It would be a lame way to go home.
- Right.

693
01:23:58,560 --> 01:24:01,199
We're gonna see Frederiks' leg.

694
01:24:01,360 --> 01:24:03,715
He has to show us.

695
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:16,073
- What's up?
- Turn around.

696
01:24:18,160 --> 01:24:21,038
Way to go, man!

697
01:24:21,200 --> 01:24:23,873
- Good to see you, Grejs.
- You, too.

698
01:24:24,040 --> 01:24:30,593
- So, are you hooked up with Brits?
- They are all bloody Afghans.

699
01:24:30,760 --> 01:24:34,753
- Even some Taliban.
- Really?

700
01:24:34,960 --> 01:24:41,069
Actually, one came in with eyes
covered and his hands tied yesterday.

701
01:24:41,240 --> 01:24:45,791
- If you go back inside, we'll come in.
See you inside.

702
01:24:45,960 --> 01:24:49,635
- Hi.
- Good to see you.

703
01:24:49,800 --> 01:24:53,634
- A well-placed shot afterwards.
- Brilliant.

704
01:24:53,800 --> 01:24:59,113
The bullet entered here
and was sticking out of my ass.

705
01:24:59,280 --> 01:25:02,397
- They had to dig it out.
- Cool.

706
01:25:02,560 --> 01:25:09,591
I totally forgot about the pain
because the chopper flew like this.

707
01:25:10,920 --> 01:25:17,792
I don't know if you heard,
but Olby got four with a grenade.

708
01:25:20,320 --> 01:25:23,676
- They were moaning.
- I don't know how many it killed.

709
01:25:23,840 --> 01:25:28,038
But three of them
were lying in a pile.

710
01:25:28,200 --> 01:25:34,435
You could only see an ear and the left
side of the head of one of them.

711
01:25:34,600 --> 01:25:39,071
The rest was hanging off him.
Two of them were underneath him.

712
01:25:39,240 --> 01:25:43,358
I thought, "What the fuck?"
They were on top of each other.

713
01:25:43,520 --> 01:25:48,469
Another was under a log,
and another was farther away.

714
01:25:48,640 --> 01:25:52,997
- He was crawling on the ground.
- No, he wasn't.

715
01:25:53,160 --> 01:25:56,994
So we hit the jackpot in that ditch.

716
01:25:57,160 --> 01:25:59,879
Okay, guys.

717
01:26:00,040 --> 01:26:02,634
Bye.

718
01:26:05,560 --> 01:26:10,111
I've got two things for you.
You definitely get the Horse.

719
01:26:10,280 --> 01:26:13,192
- Thanks a lot.
- You deserve it.

720
01:26:13,360 --> 01:26:19,230
You fought with us and with Special
Forces. Super ... Damn fine job.

721
01:26:27,600 --> 01:26:32,230
Listen up. I was questioned
by the MPs this evening.

722
01:26:35,560 --> 01:26:41,396
Apparently someone called home
and told their parents -

723
01:26:41,560 --> 01:26:44,472
- that we liquidated
wounded people -

724
01:26:44,640 --> 01:26:49,191
- and piled up the dead, to take
pictures of ourselves as heroes.

725
01:26:49,360 --> 01:26:56,277
And that I personally returned
and killed some wounded Talibans.

726
01:26:56,440 --> 01:27:01,594
People have also said that we laughed
about this during our debriefing.

727
01:27:04,480 --> 01:27:09,190
The parents ... or this mother has
contacted Operational Command -

728
01:27:09,360 --> 01:27:13,069
- and asked if that is how
we deal with things here.

729
01:27:13,240 --> 01:27:16,789
What bothers me the most
right now ...

730
01:27:19,240 --> 01:27:23,950
...is the question of loyalty.
I have to know -

731
01:27:24,120 --> 01:27:28,033
- if anyone here believes
that this is what happened.

732
01:27:28,200 --> 01:27:33,433
Does anyone honestly believe that?
Yes ...?

733
01:27:33,600 --> 01:27:39,118
If I had listened to our debriefing
and the sequence of events -

734
01:27:39,280 --> 01:27:44,308
- I would have thought
it was extremely ... delicate.

735
01:27:44,480 --> 01:27:50,749
I could understand if outsiders, who
weren't there got that impression.

736
01:27:50,920 --> 01:27:53,673
We were still on a high afterwards.

737
01:27:53,840 --> 01:27:57,116
You have to take that
into consideration.

738
01:27:57,280 --> 01:28:00,829
It was an extreme experience,
so we used extreme words.

739
01:28:01,000 --> 01:28:06,472
If the press makes a case of this,
and people think we're psychos -

740
01:28:06,640 --> 01:28:11,430
- well, let them think so.
They weren't there, they didn't see it.

741
01:28:11,600 --> 01:28:17,470
They weren't there,
but we know what happened.

742
01:28:17,640 --> 01:28:20,677
Let them talk.
They weren't there.

743
01:28:20,840 --> 01:28:24,071
If they make a case out of this,
we'll be suspended -

744
01:28:24,240 --> 01:28:29,030
- and then we'll be blowing bubbles,
and that's it until we go home.

745
01:28:29,200 --> 01:28:35,435
And we'll go down in military history,
apart from those who knew us -

746
01:28:35,600 --> 01:28:41,152
- as the guys who fucked up.
Anyone who's named in this case -

747
01:28:41,320 --> 01:28:44,153
- including myself,
Daniel and Signaler -

748
01:28:44,320 --> 01:28:50,236
- can look forward to a long session
with the whole military circus.

749
01:28:50,400 --> 01:28:54,791
"You weren't there, man" to that.

750
01:28:54,960 --> 01:29:00,034
I believe that Signaler and Daniel had
the balls to do the right thing -

751
01:29:00,200 --> 01:29:02,839
- at the right time.

752
01:29:03,000 --> 01:29:06,709
To proceed the way they did
with two wounded, one near miss -

753
01:29:06,880 --> 01:29:10,509
- and three men with holes
in their uniform and so on ...

754
01:29:10,680 --> 01:29:15,549
To walk up and shoot ... Had I seen
movement, I would have fired, too.

755
01:29:15,720 --> 01:29:21,192
And it only took Daniel or Signaler
to point under the log and say:

756
01:29:21,360 --> 01:29:23,237
"One here, one there."

757
01:29:23,400 --> 01:29:26,995
That was enough for me
to flip to automatic and shoot.

758
01:29:27,160 --> 01:29:31,676
I didn't feel like sticking my head
down to someone with a gun.

759
01:29:31,840 --> 01:29:35,355
And yes, it was touch and go.

760
01:29:35,520 --> 01:29:42,392
But in my world you do what you do.
If you have the strength not to shoot -

761
01:29:42,560 --> 01:29:46,314
- because you realize that the
movement is not that of a weapon -

762
01:29:46,480 --> 01:29:51,554
- but a surrender or whatever ... If
you have the strength to realize this -

763
01:29:51,720 --> 01:29:55,998
- you don't shoot, of course,
but had I been there -

764
01:29:56,160 --> 01:30:00,392
- I would also have fired, and
I did fire, because I wasn't sure.

765
01:30:00,560 --> 01:30:02,676
That was enough for me.

766
01:30:22,880 --> 01:30:29,513
I think it's hard for people at home
to understand how ...

767
01:30:29,680 --> 01:30:36,028
- How the decision is made?
- How you can just take a life.

768
01:30:36,200 --> 01:30:40,512
You have to be here
to understand it.

769
01:30:40,680 --> 01:30:45,310
This place is whacked, after all.
It's a fucked-up country.

770
01:30:45,480 --> 01:30:47,675
No doubt about it.

771
01:30:47,840 --> 01:30:51,913
People who understand
the war itself -

772
01:30:52,080 --> 01:30:55,789
- and how you and I and others feel
about being here -

773
01:30:55,960 --> 01:31:00,158
- and making a difference,
those people will understand us.

774
01:31:00,320 --> 01:31:06,111
Outsiders might sneer
and say that we're insane -

775
01:31:06,280 --> 01:31:09,955
- or that we did something terrible.

776
01:31:12,680 --> 01:31:15,478
I know I did the right thing.

777
01:31:15,640 --> 01:31:19,428
I know we all did the right thing.

778
01:31:53,200 --> 01:31:57,398
In case you don't know, I was
questioned by MPs this morning -

779
01:31:57,560 --> 01:32:02,588
- regarding our case with the snitch.
So far it's 'a matter of rumor' -

780
01:32:02,760 --> 01:32:08,517
- which they'll try to quash
at battalion level.

781
01:32:08,680 --> 01:32:14,073
So if you hear anything,
then dismiss it as a rumor -

782
01:32:14,240 --> 01:32:18,995
- because that's what it is.
So it's just a lot of hot air.

783
01:32:19,160 --> 01:32:22,470
It may come back to haunt us -

784
01:32:22,640 --> 01:32:26,872
- but it is a lot of hot air
without any truth in it.

785
01:32:27,760 --> 01:32:30,672
Alright?
That's it.

786
01:32:32,000 --> 01:32:34,719
Good day.

787
01:32:34,880 --> 01:32:39,476
I have a few things to say today.
First of all -

788
01:32:39,640 --> 01:32:45,078
- I'd like to award Silver and Gold
Horses for our recent engagement.

789
01:32:45,240 --> 01:32:48,835
The first two are Joe and Olby.

790
01:32:52,360 --> 01:32:58,310
Joe and Olby did something that
others might feel differently about.

791
01:32:59,000 --> 01:33:05,109
These guys did it. Five
Taliban were firing at the platoon.

792
01:33:05,280 --> 01:33:09,353
Our guys stormed them with
a hand grenade and neutralized them.

793
01:33:09,520 --> 01:33:12,353
This takes courage,
and I'm proud of you.

794
01:33:12,520 --> 01:33:16,672
I'm awarding you the Gold Horse,
and you both deserve it.

795
01:33:16,840 --> 01:33:22,472
We'll see if it leads to more.
Damn fine job.

796
01:33:23,000 --> 01:33:25,719
Congratulations.
Well deserved.

797
01:33:25,880 --> 01:33:28,519
And one for you, Joe.

798
01:33:28,680 --> 01:33:32,719
Congratulations.
You deserve it. Give them a hand.

799
01:33:44,280 --> 01:33:48,273
What does it say ...?
Smith is a part-time transvestite -

800
01:33:48,440 --> 01:33:51,159
- and a full-time idiot.

801
01:33:51,320 --> 01:33:53,959
Deep thoughts ...

802
01:33:54,960 --> 01:34:00,478
- Not a lot of deep stuff here.
- The deepest was painted over.

803
01:34:00,640 --> 01:34:05,760
The guys were a bit pissed about that.
Of course there was a lot of shit -

804
01:34:05,920 --> 01:34:09,515
- but there's also stuff which ...

805
01:34:11,200 --> 01:34:15,193
Which was quite cool to read.

806
01:34:15,360 --> 01:34:19,638
And it would be cool to see
your own stuff, if you came back.

807
01:34:21,920 --> 01:34:26,198
"In the North I know the fairest land.
My people, my home, my native land."

808
01:34:26,360 --> 01:34:30,990
"Denmark."
That was quite poetic.

809
01:36:41,400 --> 01:36:47,077
WELCOME HOME
Thanks for your efforts ...
